      <section eId="sec_CCP-5002">
        <num>CCP 5002</num>
        <heading>5002. Â Delay for appeal</heading>
        <subsection eId="CCP-5002__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>An appeal from a judgment rendered by a city court or a parish court may be taken only within ten days from the date of the judgment or from the service of notice of judgment, when such notice is necessary.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCP-5002__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>When an application for new trial is timely filed, however, the delay for appeal commences on the day after the motion is denied, or from service of notice of the order denying a new trial, when such notice is necessary.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=112135</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
